  <title>Cogl.poll_renderer_dispatch</title>
  <synopsis><code mime="text/x-gjs">
function poll_renderer_dispatch(renderer: <link xref="Cogl.Renderer">Cogl.Renderer</link>, poll_fds: <link xref="Cogl.PollFD">Cogl.PollFD</link>, n_poll_fds: Number(gint)): void {
    // Gjs wrapper for cogl_poll_renderer_dispatch()
}
  </code></synopsis>
  <p>This should be called whenever an application is woken up from
going idle in its main loop. The <code>poll_fds</code> array should contain a
list of file descriptors matched with the events that occurred in
revents. The events field is ignored. It is safe to pass in extra
file descriptors that Cogl didn't request when calling
<link xref="Cogl.poll_renderer_get_info"/> or a shorter array missing some file
descriptors that Cogl requested.</p>  <p>&lt;note&gt;If your application didn't originally create a <link xref="Cogl.Renderer"/>
manually then you can easily get a <link xref="Cogl.Renderer"/> pointer by calling
cogl_get_renderer().&lt;/note&gt;</p>
  <p>Since 1.16</p>
